  "prompt": "Why can't I answer a question twice on Quora?",
  "response": "Quora's policy typically allows users to provide one answer per question to maintain clarity and prevent redundancy. This rule helps ensure that each contribution adds unique value and avoids cluttering the thread with repetitive information. If you have additional insights, you can edit your existing answer to include new content. Alternatively, you can engage with others by commenting on their answers. This approach helps keep discussions organized and focused, ultimately enhancing the user experience on the platform.",
